تمام. الآن سنحوّل EEE Studio من “وصف” إلى **مواصفة قابلة للتشغيل الفعلي كمدخل نظام**.

هذا هو أهم تحول في المشروع: من Prompt → إلى **Executable Specification Schema**.

---

# EEE SYSTEM SPECIFICATION SCHEMA (ESS v1.0)

```text id="ess-001"
# ============================================
# EEE EXECUTABLE SYSTEM SPECIFICATION
# ESS v1.0
# ============================================

## PURPOSE

This schema defines the canonical structure used by EEE Studio to generate full enterprise AI systems.

It replaces natural language ambiguity with structured, machine-readable specifications.

--------------------------------------------------

## ROOT STRUCTURE

Every EEE system MUST follow this structure:

SYSTEM_SPEC {
    metadata
    vision
    domains
    roles
    agents
    platform
    architecture
    workflows
    events
    apis
    data
    security
    runtime
    orchestration
    governance
    validation
}
```

---

# 1. METADATA

```text id="ess-meta"
metadata {
    system_id: string
    name: string
    version: string
    description: string
    created_at: datetime
    owner: string
    classification: enum [internal, confidential, enterprise, restricted]
}
```

---

# 2. VISION LAYER

```text id="ess-vision"
vision {
    mission: string
    goals: list<string>
    success_criteria: list<string>
    constraints: list<string>
    assumptions: list<string>
}
```

---

# 3. DOMAIN MODEL

```text id="ess-domain"
domains {
    bounded_contexts: [
        {
            name: string
            purpose: string
            entities: list<string>
            value_objects: list<string>
            aggregates: list<string>
            domain_events: list<string>
            rules: list<string>
            relationships: list<string>
        }
    ]
}
```

---

# 4. ROLE MODEL (EER BASED)

```text id="ess-roles"
roles {
    role_id: string
    name: string
    responsibilities: list<string>
    inputs: list<string>
    outputs: list<string>
    permissions: list<string>
    constraints: list<string>
    domain_mapping: string
}
```

---

# 5. AGENT MODEL

```text id="ess-agents"
agents {
    agent_id: string
    role_ref: string

    capabilities: list<string>

    input_contracts: list<string>
    output_contracts: list<string>

    memory_scope: {
        short_term: boolean
        long_term: boolean
        knowledge_graph: boolean
    }

    tools: list<string>

    consumes_events: list<string>
    produces_events: list<string>

    failure_policy: {
        retry: boolean
        fallback: boolean
        escalate: boolean
    }
}
```

---

# 6. ARCHITECTURE MODEL

```text id="ess-architecture"
architecture {
    layers: [
        "EEOS",
        "UBP",
        "AIP"
    ]

    principles: list<string>

    constraints: list<string>

    integration_style: enum [
        event_driven,
        api_driven,
        hybrid
    ]
}
```

---

# 7. WORKFLOW MODEL

```text id="ess-workflow"
workflows {
    workflow_id: string
    name: string

    states: list<string>

    transitions: [
        {
            from: string
            to: string
            trigger: string
            condition: string
        }
    ]

    agents_involved: list<string>

    events_triggered: list<string>

    failure_handling: {
        retry: boolean
        compensation: boolean
        rollback: boolean
    }
}
```

---

# 8. EVENT MODEL

```text id="ess-events"
events {
    event_id: string
    name: string

    type: enum [domain, integration, system]

    version: string

    payload_schema: object

    producer: string
    consumers: list<string>

    correlation_id: boolean
}
```

---

# 9. API MODEL

```text id="ess-api"
apis {
    api_id: string
    name: string

    type: enum [rest, rpc, event, stream]

    version: string

    endpoints: [
        {
            method: string
            path: string
            request: object
            response: object
            errors: list<object>
        }
    ]

    security: {
        auth: string
        permissions: list<string>
    }
}
```

---

# 10. DATA MODEL

```text id="ess-data"
data {
    entities: list<object>

    schemas: [
        {
            name: string
            fields: list<object>
        }
    ]

    storage_model: enum [relational, document, event_store, hybrid]

    data_flows: list<object>

    ownership: string
}
```

---

# 11. SECURITY MODEL

```text id="ess-security"
security {
    model: "zero_trust"

    authentication: string
    authorization: string

    policies: list<string>

    encryption: {
        at_rest: boolean
        in_transit: boolean
    }

    audit: {
        enabled: boolean
        immutability: boolean
    }
}
```

---

# 12. RUNTIME MODEL

```text id="ess-runtime"
runtime {
    execution_model: enum [
        deterministic,
        semi_deterministic,
        event_driven
    ]

    orchestration_engine: string

    context_isolation: boolean

    failure_handling: {
        retry: boolean
        compensation: boolean
    }

    observability: {
        logs: boolean
        traces: boolean
        metrics: boolean
    }
}
```

---

# 13. ORCHESTRATION MODEL

```text id="ess-orch"
orchestration {
    topology: enum [centralized, decentralized, hybrid]

    dependency_graph: list<object>

    coordination_strategy: string

    conflict_resolution: string

    scheduling_model: string
}
```

---

# 14. GOVERNANCE MODEL

```text id="ess-gov"
governance {
    rules: list<string>

    approval_layers: list<string>

    versioning_strategy: string

    compliance: list<string>

    change_control: string
}
```

---

# 15. VALIDATION MODEL

```text id="ess-validation"
validation {
    rules: list<string>

    quality_gates: list<string>

    checks: [
        "domain_consistency",
        "event_consistency",
        "api_contract_integrity",
        "data_integrity",
        "workflow_integrity",
        "security_compliance"
    ]

    rejection_policy: string
}
```

